s:1637:"<h2>What is this?</h2>
<p>The scrolling news items at the top of the page are an instance of the Zentools2 module using the ticker layout.</p>
<p><img src="/docs/ascent2/images/frontpage/newsticker.jpg" alt="Zentools2 Newsticker" /></p>
<h4>Steps to recreate this module</h4>
<p>This module is a custom html module published to the grid8 module position.</p>
<p><strong> Module Manager </strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Navigate to the module manager in your Joomla administrator via extensions &gt; Module Manager</li>
<li>Click new</li>
<li>Select the zentools2 type module</li>
<li>Give the module a name that you will remember eg like newsticker </li>
<li>Set the module title to hide</li>
<li>Assign the module to a module position (header4).</li>
<li>Ensure the module is published</li>
</ol>
<p><img src="/docs/ascent2/images/ticker/ticker-module-settings.png" alt="Module settings" /></p>
<p><strong> Options </strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Select the ticker layout</li>
<li>Select your content source eg Joomla </li>
<li>Add the title element to the layout tools. The ticker layout works best with only the title in this position.</li>
<li>Set your desired module settings</li>
</ol>
<p><img src="/docs/ascent2/images/ticker/ticker-module-options.png" alt="Module Options" /></p>
<p><strong> Content </strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Go to the content panel</li>
<li>Adjust the content settings so that the module shows the correct content</li>
</ol>
<p><img src="/docs/ascent2/images/ticker/ticker-module-content.png" alt="Module Content" /></p>
<p><strong> Save the module </strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Click the save button in the top left of the page.</li>
</ol>";